The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on event factuality prediction (EFP), which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel graph-based neural network, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the integration of semantic and syntactic information, which is a common topic in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
